subsection.def:
suitable
                    (適合) in relation to material means approved
                by the Director as suitable for the purpose for which it is used;

paragraph.content:
in every ship in which oil or gaseous fuel is used in engines or boilers
                    for the propulsion or safety of the ship, the arrangements for the storage,
                    distribution and utilisation of the fuel shall be such that the effective use of
                    the engines can be maintained under all conditions likely to be met by the ship
                    in service;

subparagraph.content:
limited and locally earthed systems, provided that any possible
                            resulting current does not flow directly through any hazardous areas;
                            or

framing between navigation bridge windows shall be
                                                kept to a minimum and not be installed immediately
                                                forward of any workstation;
